To exclude tables in XML from docx zip in Flutter, you can modify the regex in the `getAllText()` method to exclude the `<w:tbl>` and `</w:tbl>` tags. Here's an example:

```
List<String> getAllText() {
  final regex = RegExp(r'<w:tbl>.*<\/w:tbl>');
  final textNodes = _document.findAllElements('w:t');
  final textList = <String>[];

  for (final node in textNodes) {
    final text = node.innerText ?? '';
    if (!regex.hasMatch(text)) {
      textList.add(text);
    }
  }
  return textList;
}
```

This will exclude any text nodes that are enclosed by `<w:tbl>` and `</w:tbl>` tags, which are used to represent tables in docx files.
